Description: Linux client compatible with PowerToys Mouse Without Borders
 mwb-linux lets a Linux desktop share keyboard, mouse, and clipboard with a
 Windows machine running Microsoft PowerToys Mouse Without Borders.
 .
 It implements the compatible network protocol from Linux, injects inbound
 input through uinput, and supports bidirectional cursor and keyboard control
 on X11 sessions.
